                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10678: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-13T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 13, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>…There is no intimation as yet of reopening navigation on West River. British
                    gunboat <hi rend="italic">Sea Mew</hi> is now en route to Wuchow with food
                    supplies for foreigners, including Americans if needed.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
